
This web application allows users to upload images to Wikimedia Commons using the MediaWiki API.
We respect your privacy and keep your data safe.
1. Information We Collect
•	Uploaded images and the metadata you provide (title, description, categories).
•	Temporary technical logs for performance and debugging.
2. How We Use Your Information
•	To process and upload your image to Wikimedia Commons.
•	To improve the app’s performance and fix errors.
3. Data Storage
•	We do not store your Wikimedia login credentials.
•	Uploaded images are sent directly to Wikimedia Commons, where they become public.
•	No permanent copies of your files are saved on our server.
4. Third-Party Services
Uploads are handled through the Wikimedia Commons MediaWiki API.
Wikimedia’s privacy policy also applies.
5. Your Choices
You may stop using the app at any time.
You can edit or delete your uploaded files directly on Wikimedia Commons.
6. Contact
For questions, contact: [https://github.com/Wiki-For-All-Technical]
